Taiwan, US tourist study groups arrive in North Korea 
Taiwan and US tourist study groups arrived in Pyongyang Tuesday for an
international festival scheduled for April in the North Korean capital,
a report said.
The Korean Central News Agency report said that the Taiwan group was
led by Chang Shihliang, president of the China Cross-Straits Industrial
Association, while the US group was headed by Thomas Boehm, vice
president of the Carlson Wagonlit Development Company.
It said: "The study groups consist of nearly 30 members including
business officials and reporters."
The Taiwan and US groups will make several study trips until March 4 in
North Korea, the agency said.
The Pyongyang International Sports and Cultural Festival is scheduled
for April 28-30.
